1
00:00:00,470 --> 00:00:02,740
By the way, Mom, did your car break down?

2
00:00:02,740 --> 00:00:03,980
(Episode 38)

3
00:00:03,980 --> 00:00:04,980
What?

4
00:00:05,180 --> 00:00:07,080
I heard you mention a wrench.

5
00:00:07,410 --> 00:00:08,410
What?

6
00:00:08,950 --> 00:00:11,250
"Did you hide it well?
The wrench, I mean."

7
00:00:11,250 --> 00:00:12,450
That's what you said, Mom.

8
00:00:13,690 --> 00:00:15,950
What are you talking about?

9
00:00:16,090 --> 00:00:17,360
I never said anything like that.

10
00:00:18,390 --> 00:00:19,690
Maybe you're talking about...

11
00:00:19,690 --> 00:00:21,990
the mass spam email incident
that Manager Lee reported to me.

12
00:00:22,490 --> 00:00:23,560
That's been taken care of.

13
00:00:24,330 --> 00:00:27,630
Besides, if my car broke down,
do you really think I'd fix it myself?

14
00:00:27,870 --> 00:00:29,370
That's ridiculous.

15
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:34,640
You're right. I guess I just misheard it
when I was half-asleep last night.

16
00:00:34,870 --> 00:00:36,980
It's not something to get
so worked up about.

17
00:00:37,980 --> 00:00:41,080
I guess CEO Chae has been on edge lately.

18
00:00:42,580 --> 00:00:45,650
You don't look like
you're on your deathbed,

19
00:00:45,650 --> 00:00:46,820
seeing how worked up you are.

20
00:00:47,120 --> 00:00:49,790
Right. Don't worry. I'm perfectly healthy.

21
00:00:50,620 --> 00:00:53,190
Father, I have something
I need to discuss with you.

22
00:00:58,130 --> 00:01:01,370
Do you want to promote Chef Kang Jun Ho
to general manager?

23
00:01:01,370 --> 00:01:02,370
Oh, my!

24
00:01:05,900 --> 00:01:07,840
Yes.
I'd like to appoint Chef Kang Jun Ho...

25
00:01:07,840 --> 00:01:09,840
as general manager
of our hotel's kitchen brand.

26
00:01:10,140 --> 00:01:11,810
And I want to make
the official announcement.

27
00:01:12,110 --> 00:01:14,180
So you're just reporting this to me?

28
00:01:15,380 --> 00:01:17,680
Why did you make that decision?

29
00:01:17,880 --> 00:01:20,790
For one, Seo Rin can't seem
to focus on her work at all.

30
00:01:20,890 --> 00:01:22,050
I've been told.

31
00:01:22,650 --> 00:01:25,590
Apparently, she's been punching
the clock at Chang Restaurant.

32
00:01:25,860 --> 00:01:27,690
We may have renovated Dream Hotel,

33
00:01:28,060 --> 00:01:29,990
but all the internal board members
are still there.

34
00:01:30,600 --> 00:01:33,770
At this rate, for Seo Rin to be
the successor of Dream Group,

35
00:01:34,100 --> 00:01:35,870
the board will never accept her.

36
00:01:37,770 --> 00:01:39,070
I imagine there will be some pushback.

37
00:01:39,370 --> 00:01:43,310
From what I've gathered, Chef Kang Jun Ho
is quite capable in many respects.

38
00:01:45,980 --> 00:01:49,650
So you want him to work with Seo Rin?

39
00:01:49,650 --> 00:01:50,650
Yes.

40
00:01:51,050 --> 00:01:53,150
We need young talent, Father.

41
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:57,490
But what if Kang Jun Ho gets ambitious
and tries to play Seo Rin?

42
00:01:57,760 --> 00:01:59,890
What will you do then?
Will you take responsibility?

43
00:02:00,230 --> 00:02:01,460
Father, you know her.

44
00:02:02,060 --> 00:02:03,800
Seo Rin is resilient.

45
00:02:04,360 --> 00:02:06,660
Besides, she's no pushover.

46
00:02:07,370 --> 00:02:10,770
That's true. Seo Rin is a smart girl.

47
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:14,410
Why don't you try
trusting Seo Rin this time?

48
00:02:15,340 --> 00:02:17,910
I'll keep a close eye on Kang Jun Ho.

49
00:02:18,980 --> 00:02:20,140
Well...

50
00:02:20,140 --> 00:02:22,350
It's a big gamble...

51
00:02:23,010 --> 00:02:27,550
And don't you dare let this lead
to a wedding. Understood?

52
00:02:27,650 --> 00:02:30,050
Yes, Father. I'll make sure of it.

53
00:02:31,020 --> 00:02:34,090
That came out of left field.

54
00:02:35,130 --> 00:02:36,860
She was against him
like her life depended on it,

55
00:02:36,860 --> 00:02:38,200
and now she's promoting him?

56
00:02:38,260 --> 00:02:39,260
Does that make any sense?

57
00:02:40,300 --> 00:02:44,170
And as if that's not enough,
she's letting him date Seo Rin?

58
00:02:45,140 --> 00:02:46,440
How bizarre.

59
00:02:46,940 --> 00:02:49,640
And after she treated Jun Ho
like a thorn in her side.

60
00:02:50,340 --> 00:02:52,310
It's absolutely ridiculous.

61
00:02:53,040 --> 00:02:54,310
Goodness!

62
00:02:55,310 --> 00:02:56,310
You!

63
00:02:59,150 --> 00:03:02,190
Hwa Young, you should learn to knock.

64
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:06,520
Why do you always just barge in
and give me a heart attack?

65
00:03:06,590 --> 00:03:08,530
A woman of your supposed refinement.

66
00:03:08,860 --> 00:03:09,930
Yeom San Wol.

67
00:03:09,990 --> 00:03:11,100
Jin Hong Ju.

68
00:03:11,530 --> 00:03:13,730
I'm putting this on hold for now.

69
00:03:13,870 --> 00:03:15,430
What are you talking about?

70
00:03:15,500 --> 00:03:16,800
Jin Hong Ju, I'm sure you were put up...

71
00:03:17,270 --> 00:03:19,940
to searching my office by your mother.

72
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:22,110
I was looking for a nail clipper...

73
00:03:22,170 --> 00:03:24,010
From now on,
you two had better walk on eggshells.

74
00:03:24,780 --> 00:03:26,640
If you step out of line one more time,

75
00:03:27,580 --> 00:03:29,710
I will drag you both to the fiery pit.
Mark my words.

76
00:03:36,750 --> 00:03:39,120
Drag us to the fiery pit? How terrifying.

77
00:03:39,590 --> 00:03:43,560
Is she losing her mind?
Why is she acting so out of character?

78
00:03:43,760 --> 00:03:46,630
After making such a huge fuss
about how much she hated that chef.

79
00:03:46,700 --> 00:03:48,130
Something is definitely off.

80
00:03:48,670 --> 00:03:49,870
Something smells fishy.

81
00:03:50,570 --> 00:03:51,570
I know, right?

82
00:03:52,540 --> 00:03:54,740
(Police)

83
00:03:55,010 --> 00:03:56,510
Tae Pyung!

84
00:03:56,740 --> 00:03:58,410
Calm down.

85
00:03:58,610 --> 00:04:00,480
If you go in there swinging,
you'll be in big trouble.

86
00:04:00,850 --> 00:04:02,610
Let me find out what's going on first.

87
00:04:02,810 --> 00:04:03,950
What's there to find out?

88
00:04:04,520 --> 00:04:06,050
I'm not going to let the guy
who hit my dad with a car...

89
00:04:06,550 --> 00:04:07,820
get away with this.

90
00:04:08,220 --> 00:04:09,220
Hey, hold on.

91
00:04:10,050 --> 00:04:11,060
I said, let go!

92
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:12,890
I'll contact you again
when Mr. Oh Bok Gil wakes up.

93
00:04:13,190 --> 00:04:15,890
The investigation is still ongoing,
so please don't go too far.

94
00:04:16,430 --> 00:04:18,230
- Okay.
- Right. Thank you.

95
00:04:23,130 --> 00:04:25,740
Hey, you bastard.
Did you hit my dad with your car?

96
00:04:25,900 --> 00:04:27,610
How can you be so uncivilized?

97
00:04:27,870 --> 00:04:31,180
Your father was drunk and passed out
in the middle of the road.

98
00:04:31,310 --> 00:04:33,280
My husband is a victim here too, you know!

99
00:04:33,380 --> 00:04:36,150
What? That's completely ridiculous.

100
00:04:36,550 --> 00:04:37,550
Mom?

101
00:04:39,620 --> 00:04:41,150
Oh my gosh, honey!

102
00:04:41,950 --> 00:04:43,690
- Are you okay?
- My dad...

103
00:04:44,690 --> 00:04:45,820
is dying right now.

104
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:48,430
You were drinking and driving,
weren't you?

105
00:04:48,760 --> 00:04:50,130
You were definitely drunk driving.

106
00:04:50,430 --> 00:04:52,030
That makes you
a potential murderer, right?

107
00:04:52,100 --> 00:04:54,830
Your father was the one who was drunk
and lying in the street!

108
00:04:54,900 --> 00:04:56,870
Your father is the one who ruined my life!

109
00:04:56,930 --> 00:04:58,670
You think you can just run your mouth off
like that?

110
00:04:59,570 --> 00:05:00,870
If my dad dies,

111
00:05:01,570 --> 00:05:02,570
you!

112
00:05:04,340 --> 00:05:05,810
You're a dead man.

113
00:05:05,810 --> 00:05:08,150
Let go of him and just talk!

114
00:05:08,680 --> 00:05:10,250
Baek Ho, why are you standing there?

115
00:05:10,250 --> 00:05:11,350
Dad...

116
00:05:11,580 --> 00:05:12,980
What's going on?

117
00:05:18,320 --> 00:05:20,360
Dad, are you really the one
who caused the accident?

118
00:05:21,090 --> 00:05:22,090
What?

119
00:05:23,730 --> 00:05:24,730
Baek Ho...

120
00:05:25,630 --> 00:05:26,660
He's your father?

121
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:28,270
Let go of him now!

122
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:01,500
The surgery went well,

123
00:06:02,430 --> 00:06:03,970
but we need to monitor his progress.

124
00:06:05,770 --> 00:06:06,800
Tonight...

125
00:06:07,370 --> 00:06:08,710
could be critical.

126
00:06:28,030 --> 00:06:30,500
Father, please...

127
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:33,230
Please save my dad.

128
00:06:34,370 --> 00:06:35,770
They said tonight was critical.

129
00:06:36,530 --> 00:06:37,900
My poor dad.

130
00:06:39,140 --> 00:06:42,670
He never even ate properly
or dressed properly for himself.

131
00:06:43,470 --> 00:06:45,340
He took in my mother and me.

132
00:06:45,910 --> 00:06:48,450
He's a wonderful man
who took such good care of us.

133
00:06:49,580 --> 00:06:52,220
I never even got a chance
to repay his kindness,

134
00:06:53,150 --> 00:06:56,120
so he can't die so senselessly and soon.

135
00:06:57,620 --> 00:06:58,620
Father,

136
00:06:59,290 --> 00:07:00,290
please...

137
00:07:01,260 --> 00:07:02,590
Please let my dad...

138
00:07:03,330 --> 00:07:05,460
get through this critical time,
bounce back,

139
00:07:06,230 --> 00:07:07,600
and get back on his feet.

140
00:07:09,500 --> 00:07:10,500
Father.

141
00:07:11,340 --> 00:07:12,340
Please...

142
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:14,510
Please...

143
00:07:24,080 --> 00:07:26,680
Go wash up and get some rest.
You must be exhausted.

144
00:07:28,150 --> 00:07:29,850
Honey, I'm so sorry.

145
00:07:30,560 --> 00:07:32,460
You must be worried sick.

146
00:07:32,920 --> 00:07:34,260
It's okay.

147
00:07:35,330 --> 00:07:38,560
You turned yourself in
right after the accident,

148
00:07:38,900 --> 00:07:42,070
and you submitted both your statement
and the dashcam footage.

149
00:07:42,230 --> 00:07:45,170
Since turning yourself in is generally not
punished with detention under the law,

150
00:07:45,170 --> 00:07:46,570
you shouldn't have much trouble.

151
00:07:47,870 --> 00:07:50,840
So, it means I don't have to
go to prison, right?

152
00:07:51,780 --> 00:07:53,410
But if the victim passes away,

153
00:07:54,110 --> 00:07:55,410
you could go to prison.

154
00:07:57,520 --> 00:08:01,450
I really hope he makes it.

155
00:08:02,550 --> 00:08:03,550
He has to.

156
00:08:05,890 --> 00:08:07,090
By the way,

157
00:08:07,590 --> 00:08:09,560
you said you were heading to the school.

158
00:08:09,560 --> 00:08:11,160
What were you doing there at that hour?

159
00:08:12,530 --> 00:08:15,500
I said I went there
for the Dream Resort business.

160
00:08:15,970 --> 00:08:19,700
I told the detective that many times.
Do I have to say it all again to you?

161
00:08:20,140 --> 00:08:21,140
Okay, fine.

162
00:08:21,770 --> 00:08:25,140
In any case,
a legal battle may be unavoidable.

163
00:08:25,740 --> 00:08:27,580
You need to brace yourself.

164
00:08:28,510 --> 00:08:29,510
I will.

165
00:08:30,980 --> 00:08:33,180
- Thank you.
- Honey.

166
00:08:33,680 --> 00:08:34,750
You poor thing.

167
00:08:35,820 --> 00:08:37,720
It was just rotten luck.

168
00:08:38,490 --> 00:08:39,990
Hang in there, okay?

169
00:08:48,230 --> 00:08:49,230
Hello, Jun Ho.

170
00:08:50,030 --> 00:08:51,470
Your dad just got home.

171
00:08:52,370 --> 00:08:54,870
He was released pending investigation.

172
00:08:55,870 --> 00:08:56,870
I see.

173
00:08:57,510 --> 00:08:58,610
Is Father okay?

174
00:08:59,980 --> 00:09:02,750
He must be exhausted
after being questioned all night.

175
00:09:06,620 --> 00:09:07,720
Yes, he is.

176
00:09:07,850 --> 00:09:09,120
But get this,

177
00:09:09,920 --> 00:09:13,090
Baek Ho's friends with the victim's son.

178
00:09:13,090 --> 00:09:14,190
What?

179
00:09:14,660 --> 00:09:15,990
The victim's son?

180
00:09:16,260 --> 00:09:17,260
That's right.

181
00:09:17,760 --> 00:09:20,560
He grabbed your dad by the collar
in the police station...

182
00:09:20,770 --> 00:09:23,130
and made a huge scene, calling him
a potential murderer and everything.

183
00:09:23,500 --> 00:09:24,670
It's just unbelievable.

184
00:09:25,270 --> 00:09:27,640
His father was the one who was drunk
and lying in the street, after all.

185
00:09:27,970 --> 00:09:28,970
Honestly.

186
00:09:29,270 --> 00:09:31,440
What kind of twisted fate is this?

187
00:09:31,440 --> 00:09:33,640
That's not fate, Mom. That's a curse.

188
00:09:34,580 --> 00:09:35,980
Anyway, Mother, you've been through a lot.

189
00:09:36,110 --> 00:09:38,150
I shouldn't hold you up
when you're so busy.

190
00:09:39,050 --> 00:09:40,820
Okay, I'll let you go. Get back to work.

191
00:09:42,990 --> 00:09:45,320
An all-night questioning?
What's happening?

192
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:46,460
It's nothing you need to worry about.

193
00:09:46,660 --> 00:09:49,130
What kind of case is it?
You said there was a victim.

194
00:09:49,460 --> 00:09:52,730
Then, is your family the one at fault,
Jun Ho?

195
00:09:53,970 --> 00:09:54,970
Aren't you leaving?

196
00:09:55,700 --> 00:09:57,500
Do you think this is your playground,
Director Ma?

197
00:09:58,400 --> 00:10:00,140
Oh my, how did you know?

198
00:10:00,400 --> 00:10:03,540
I've treated this hotel as my playground
since I was a little girl.

199
00:10:16,150 --> 00:10:17,150
Tae Pyung.

200
00:10:22,130 --> 00:10:23,130
Jang Mi.

201
00:10:24,730 --> 00:10:26,460
Don't even think about
seeing Kang Baek Ho ever again.

202
00:10:27,600 --> 00:10:28,700
What are you talking about?

203
00:10:28,700 --> 00:10:30,170
That bastard Lawyer Kang's father...

204
00:10:32,370 --> 00:10:34,470
is the suspect
who hit our dad with his car.

205
00:10:36,040 --> 00:10:37,040
What?

206
00:10:38,410 --> 00:10:39,410
Our dad...

207
00:10:40,380 --> 00:10:42,650
is lying there, unable to move a muscle,

208
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:45,650
but the man who ran him over walked free
just because he turned himself in.

209
00:10:47,350 --> 00:10:48,390
No way!

210
00:10:49,120 --> 00:10:50,590
How could it be Baek Ho's father?

211
00:10:58,330 --> 00:11:00,360
At that time of night,
why was Jang Mi's father...

212
00:11:00,970 --> 00:11:02,600
in such an unfamiliar location?

213
00:11:03,070 --> 00:11:05,640
We'd have to check his cell phone
to find out why he was there,

214
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:07,270
but it hasn't been found yet.

215
00:11:08,440 --> 00:11:11,210
For now, we're working
with his phone company to investigate.

216
00:11:15,650 --> 00:11:17,780
And what did my dad say?

217
00:11:19,080 --> 00:11:22,020
He said he was on his way to the resort
he was consulting for.

218
00:11:23,120 --> 00:11:27,760
His assistant confirmed that he was
working on a project with Dream Hotel.

219
00:11:28,760 --> 00:11:31,360
We won't know for sure...

220
00:11:31,360 --> 00:11:33,400
until we get his travel route
and call records.

221
00:11:33,660 --> 00:11:34,670
Correct.

222
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:37,740
Lawyer Kang, you did so much
to help Ms. Oh Jang Mi.

223
00:11:38,540 --> 00:11:40,300
This whole situation
must be tearing you up.

224
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:44,210
I just don't understand
how something like this could happen.

225
00:11:45,780 --> 00:11:48,280
- But something feels off.
- What?

226
00:11:48,580 --> 00:11:51,780
From what I know,
Jang Mi's father rarely drinks.

227
00:11:52,380 --> 00:11:55,950
So him being drunk enough to lie in a road
just doesn't add up.

228
00:11:55,950 --> 00:11:57,090
All the way out there, no less.

229
00:11:57,090 --> 00:12:01,060
Lawyer Kang, you deal with people
for a living, so you must know.

230
00:12:01,390 --> 00:12:03,930
People aren't always
what they seem on the surface.

231
00:12:03,930 --> 00:12:06,430
My dad would never drink enough
to get that drunk.

232
00:12:06,560 --> 00:12:08,100
He's never, ever done
anything like that before.

233
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:09,700
Something is very wrong with this.

234
00:12:10,940 --> 00:12:11,940
Jang Mi.

235
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,410
Where did the accident happen?

236
00:12:14,870 --> 00:12:17,680
Please give me the exact address.
I'm going to go see for myself.

237
00:12:18,310 --> 00:12:19,840
I'm telling you this whole situation
makes no sense.

238
00:12:19,840 --> 00:12:21,180
Jang Mi, please, calm down.

239
00:12:21,250 --> 00:12:22,310
And another thing. My dad...

240
00:12:23,250 --> 00:12:24,520
called me...

241
00:12:25,680 --> 00:12:26,950
right before the accident.

242
00:12:27,650 --> 00:12:29,820
- He did?
- He called you?

243
00:12:30,420 --> 00:12:32,290
But you just said his phone wasn't found.

244
00:12:32,720 --> 00:12:33,790
That's right.

245
00:12:34,020 --> 00:12:35,930
He was struggling...

246
00:12:36,490 --> 00:12:37,930
to tell me something,

247
00:12:38,830 --> 00:12:40,330
but then he suddenly screamed,

248
00:12:42,430 --> 00:12:44,240
and then the line just went dead.

249
00:12:56,380 --> 00:12:57,550
What's this about?

250
00:12:59,020 --> 00:13:01,820
I believe I've given you plenty of time
to think.

251
00:13:02,190 --> 00:13:05,490
Have you made a decision
about the promotion to General Manager?

252
00:13:05,790 --> 00:13:08,560
I have to ask why you're suddenly
making me this offer.

253
00:13:08,660 --> 00:13:09,790
I already told you.

254
00:13:10,460 --> 00:13:12,300
I highly regard your skills, Chef Kang.

255
00:13:12,300 --> 00:13:13,300
No.

256
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:16,070
That's not a good enough reason for me.

257
00:13:16,700 --> 00:13:20,600
Besides, the guests at Chang Restaurant
come specifically for me,

258
00:13:21,170 --> 00:13:23,140
so I'd like to honor their reservations.

259
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:28,750
I can't irresponsibly turn away guests
who made reservations to see me.

260
00:13:29,280 --> 00:13:30,280
Excellent.

261
00:13:30,850 --> 00:13:32,620
I'm telling you,
I'm a great judge of character.

262
00:13:32,750 --> 00:13:35,950
You're so responsible and passionate
about your work, Chef Kang.

263
00:13:36,320 --> 00:13:38,160
That's the very reason I'm promoting you.

264
00:13:43,930 --> 00:13:45,430
Jun Ho.

265
00:13:48,400 --> 00:13:49,400
What's this?

266
00:13:54,240 --> 00:13:55,310
So bored.

267
00:13:58,180 --> 00:14:00,810
Did you hide it well?
The wrench, I mean.

268
00:14:01,410 --> 00:14:03,750
I'm sure I heard it loud and clear,

269
00:14:04,350 --> 00:14:06,220
so why does Mom keep denying it?

270
00:14:06,420 --> 00:14:07,890
Maybe you're talking about...

271
00:14:07,890 --> 00:14:10,120
the mass spam email incident
that Manager Lee reported to me.

272
00:14:11,890 --> 00:14:12,990
Spam emails?

273
00:14:13,420 --> 00:14:14,860
That's ridiculous.

274
00:14:16,230 --> 00:14:20,500
But why does she keep lying?
What's the big deal with that wrench?

275
00:14:22,670 --> 00:14:25,400
First things first,
I need to grill Manager Lee.

276
00:14:26,840 --> 00:14:27,840
This is going to be fun.

277
00:14:29,540 --> 00:14:31,810
There's nothing new
on Oh Jang Mi's side, right?

278
00:14:32,080 --> 00:14:34,580
Correct. Oh Bok Gil is still in a coma.

279
00:14:35,550 --> 00:14:36,580
Tell your guys...

280
00:14:37,250 --> 00:14:38,780
to look it over carefully.

281
00:14:38,780 --> 00:14:39,950
Thanks, sir.

282
00:14:41,850 --> 00:14:43,990
Seo Rin,
when will you ever learn some manners?

283
00:14:44,590 --> 00:14:46,760
How can you expect to become
the head of Dream like that?

284
00:14:47,930 --> 00:14:49,190
Like this is anything new.

285
00:14:50,330 --> 00:14:52,530
You need to carry yourself
with the dignity of your position.

286
00:14:53,430 --> 00:14:54,470
Whatever.

287
00:14:54,770 --> 00:14:57,370
Where's Manager Lee?
I don't see him around.

288
00:14:57,370 --> 00:14:59,240
Why the sudden interest in him?

289
00:14:59,400 --> 00:15:02,510
I was in the control room yesterday,
and an employee there said...

290
00:15:02,710 --> 00:15:04,580
that Manager Lee had been there
just a little while before me.

291
00:15:05,810 --> 00:15:07,950
What were you doing in the control room?

292
00:15:08,110 --> 00:15:10,110
Mom, is your memory going?

293
00:15:10,110 --> 00:15:14,120
I told you that people keep calling me
Jang Mi or something.

294
00:15:14,180 --> 00:15:17,420
I wanted to find that guy who carried
around all that smelly stuff...

295
00:15:17,420 --> 00:15:18,520
and go give him a piece of my mind.

296
00:15:18,620 --> 00:15:20,420
So, did you check?

297
00:15:20,490 --> 00:15:21,630
Who do you take me for?

298
00:15:21,860 --> 00:15:25,330
I took a picture of the bags
he was carrying off the CCTV,

299
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:27,560
found the address on it, and went there.

300
00:15:27,770 --> 00:15:30,670
What? You actually went to
that side dish shop?

301
00:15:30,800 --> 00:15:34,610
Oh my. How did you know it was
a side dish shop, Mom?

302
00:15:35,810 --> 00:15:37,740
You mentioned it this morning.

303
00:15:38,740 --> 00:15:39,980
Did I?

304
00:15:40,410 --> 00:15:43,350
So what do you want with Manager Lee?

305
00:15:44,480 --> 00:15:46,320
Mom, why are you so tense?

306
00:15:46,820 --> 00:15:48,420
Are you hiding something from me?

307
00:15:48,720 --> 00:15:51,160
- You're acting kind of strange.
- What's so strange about me?

308
00:15:51,560 --> 00:15:53,460
I asked you why you're looking
for Manager Lee.

309
00:15:54,390 --> 00:15:58,360
I was just curious why he went
to the control room, so I thought I'd ask.

310
00:16:00,030 --> 00:16:01,370
Of all the things to be curious about.

311
00:16:02,300 --> 00:16:04,740
Don't you know he oversees
all hotel operations?

312
00:16:05,500 --> 00:16:08,240
In case you didn't know,

313
00:16:08,310 --> 00:16:09,810
just a while ago, Chef Kang Jun Ho...

314
00:16:10,270 --> 00:16:12,410
accepted the promotion to General Manager.

315
00:16:14,810 --> 00:16:17,950
- Great.
- Learn the business by his side...

316
00:16:18,220 --> 00:16:20,080
and get him on your side. Got it?

317
00:16:20,450 --> 00:16:21,450
I will.

318
00:16:21,650 --> 00:16:24,920
I feel so energized now that
you're backing me up.

319
00:16:26,560 --> 00:16:28,530
I get it. You can count on me, Mom.

320
00:16:29,060 --> 00:16:30,160
Congratulations.

321
00:16:30,590 --> 00:16:33,460
After all, you're the one
who saved Chang Restaurant.

322
00:16:34,400 --> 00:16:35,800
You more than earned this promotion.

323
00:16:35,900 --> 00:16:38,770
You're not just happy about getting credit
for scouting me, are you?

324
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:41,170
Well, that's part of it.

325
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:45,180
Thanks to you, I'm getting brownie points
for my eye for talent.

326
00:16:46,310 --> 00:16:47,310
Right.

327
00:16:49,080 --> 00:16:51,120
I'm still suspicious of CEO Chae, though.

328
00:16:51,250 --> 00:16:54,620
It's not our place to question
what the higher-ups are thinking.

329
00:16:54,820 --> 00:16:57,620
You got that disastrous Chang Restaurant
running smoothly,

330
00:16:57,620 --> 00:16:59,360
now as General Manager,

331
00:16:59,560 --> 00:17:01,790
you should aim even higher,
don't you think?

332
00:17:02,560 --> 00:17:04,500
I think this is a great opportunity
for you.

333
00:17:04,700 --> 00:17:08,600
I'll give some more thought to
what I can accomplish as General Manager.

334
00:17:09,270 --> 00:17:12,040
By the way, how's it going
with that guy you're into?

335
00:17:13,340 --> 00:17:16,040
I don't know. He's a tough nut to crack.

336
00:17:17,270 --> 00:17:19,180
So I'm trying a more roundabout strategy.

337
00:17:19,940 --> 00:17:20,980
Well...

338
00:17:21,280 --> 00:17:22,610
I'd say I'm about halfway there.

339
00:17:24,480 --> 00:17:25,720
What's so complicated about it?

340
00:17:26,380 --> 00:17:27,990
(National Police Agency)

341
00:17:28,790 --> 00:17:29,790
Hey, wait up.

342
00:17:30,090 --> 00:17:31,590
I said I'd give you a ride.

343
00:17:31,590 --> 00:17:32,720
I said I was fine.

344
00:17:33,260 --> 00:17:34,990
Why would I get in a car with you?

345
00:17:36,030 --> 00:17:37,260
You and I...

346
00:17:38,300 --> 00:17:39,700
are nothing to each other anymore.

347
00:17:40,630 --> 00:17:43,170
- Besides, my dad...
- I'm sorry. I really am,

348
00:17:44,640 --> 00:17:46,400
but the full story will come out later.

349
00:17:47,300 --> 00:17:48,310
For now,

350
00:17:48,940 --> 00:17:50,510
I need to go see your father too,

351
00:17:51,440 --> 00:17:52,480
so let's go to the hospital together.

352
00:17:52,510 --> 00:17:55,480
What makes you think you'll be welcome
at my father's hospital?

353
00:17:56,350 --> 00:17:57,410
I said to forget it.

354
00:18:07,620 --> 00:18:09,230
Director Ma was in the control room?

355
00:18:09,590 --> 00:18:12,860
Yes. From the look on her face,
I don't think she saw anything.

356
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:16,670
- But still...
- The CCTVs in the parking lot were off,

357
00:18:16,700 --> 00:18:18,140
so no one saw anything.

358
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:19,840
If Oh Bok Gil dies,

359
00:18:20,700 --> 00:18:22,440
the police will launch
an investigation, right?

360
00:18:23,070 --> 00:18:24,210
I'll be prepared for that.

361
00:18:24,680 --> 00:18:26,640
Seo Rin is making me even more worried.

362
00:18:27,710 --> 00:18:29,750
That girl has incredible instincts,

363
00:18:30,050 --> 00:18:32,150
and this morning
she even brought up the wrench.

364
00:18:33,320 --> 00:18:35,320
I just hope she doesn't
start poking around.

365
00:18:39,090 --> 00:18:42,890
How can anyone think
they're just business partners?

366
00:18:44,430 --> 00:18:46,830
I'm sure of it.
Chae Hwa Young is seeing this guy.

367
00:18:47,530 --> 00:18:49,030
My gut is never wrong.

368
00:18:49,230 --> 00:18:52,900
What are you staring at and muttering?

369
00:18:52,900 --> 00:18:54,100
It's nothing.

370
00:18:55,010 --> 00:18:56,040
Good grief.

371
00:18:57,710 --> 00:19:01,350
I need to keep my mouth shut
until I have concrete proof.

372
00:19:03,350 --> 00:19:04,350
Chairman.

373
00:19:08,520 --> 00:19:11,190
I was thinking maybe we should go
on a trip to a hot spring,

374
00:19:11,490 --> 00:19:13,660
- so I was looking at some places.
- A hot spring?

375
00:19:14,020 --> 00:19:15,030
Sounds great.

376
00:19:15,060 --> 00:19:19,460
I heard they have co-ed ones now
that are really nice.

377
00:19:20,400 --> 00:19:21,970
With you, Mrs. Yeom?

378
00:19:23,900 --> 00:19:26,140
Why? Are you feeling shy, Chairman?

379
00:19:27,640 --> 00:19:29,110
It sounds lovely to me.

380
00:19:29,940 --> 00:19:31,310
Alright, let's go.

381
00:19:31,980 --> 00:19:33,040
But before that,

382
00:19:33,340 --> 00:19:35,480
there's somewhere we need to go first.

383
00:19:35,480 --> 00:19:36,580
Oh my!

384
00:19:37,350 --> 00:19:38,580
Where to?

385
00:19:43,190 --> 00:19:44,190
Oh my.

386
00:19:46,460 --> 00:19:47,560
Oh my.

387
00:19:50,860 --> 00:19:51,860
Oh my.

388
00:19:54,330 --> 00:19:57,330
- I'm here to pick up an order.
- Right away, sir.

389
00:19:58,740 --> 00:20:00,170
Oh my goodness.

390
00:20:00,900 --> 00:20:04,810
Chairman,
you didn't forget about me after all.

391
00:20:05,080 --> 00:20:07,040
This was all part of your plan, wasn't it?

392
00:20:07,840 --> 00:20:09,310
Thank you, Chairman.

393
00:20:10,750 --> 00:20:11,750
Oh my.

394
00:20:12,680 --> 00:20:15,090
That's right.
I need to keep Mrs. Yeom close.

395
00:20:15,150 --> 00:20:18,190
It's the only way I can figure out
what CEO Chae is up to.

396
00:20:19,090 --> 00:20:21,590
- It's time for the carrot, not the stick.
- It's so pretty.

397
00:20:21,830 --> 00:20:22,860
Absolutely.

398
00:20:40,410 --> 00:20:42,710
Doctor, the patient's blood pressure
is dropping rapidly.

399
00:20:42,780 --> 00:20:45,020
Get the epinephrine ready
and reconnect the EKG.

400
00:20:45,020 --> 00:20:46,050
Yes.

401
00:20:50,650 --> 00:20:53,520
Jang Mi, Dad's in critical condition.
Get to the hospital now.

402
00:20:54,190 --> 00:20:55,190
Dad.

403
00:20:56,030 --> 00:20:58,330
- What are we going to do?
- It's going to be okay.

404
00:20:59,730 --> 00:21:00,730
Dad...

405
00:21:01,030 --> 00:21:02,200
Dad!

406
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:06,670
(ICU Family Waiting Room)

407
00:21:12,680 --> 00:21:13,740
Dad.

408
00:21:14,650 --> 00:21:15,750
He'll be okay.

409
00:21:32,460 --> 00:21:33,760
Doctor, we've got him back.

410
00:21:39,500 --> 00:21:40,500
Tae Pyung.

411
00:21:41,640 --> 00:21:42,770
He's going to be okay.

412
00:21:43,710 --> 00:21:44,910
Everything is going to be okay.

413
00:21:50,580 --> 00:21:51,580
Doctor.

414
00:21:52,180 --> 00:21:53,620
How's our dad?

415
00:21:53,680 --> 00:21:54,920
He's okay now, right?

416
00:21:54,990 --> 00:21:56,450
He's out of the woods for now,

417
00:21:57,290 --> 00:21:58,460
but if this happens again,

418
00:21:59,160 --> 00:22:00,360
I can't make any guarantees.

419
00:22:01,120 --> 00:22:02,130
What do you mean?

420
00:22:04,730 --> 00:22:05,730
Jang Mi.

421
00:22:08,570 --> 00:22:09,730
What are you doing here?

422
00:22:10,100 --> 00:22:12,700
Did your father send you to check
if my dad was dead?

423
00:22:12,770 --> 00:22:13,770
Tae Pyung.

424
00:22:15,270 --> 00:22:17,610
Just leave.
Leave while I'm asking you nicely.

425
00:22:18,340 --> 00:22:19,840
I don't want to see your face again!

426
00:22:21,140 --> 00:22:22,150
Baek Ho.

427
00:22:23,550 --> 00:22:25,180
I think it's best if you leave.

428
00:22:26,120 --> 00:22:27,250
Jang Mi.

429
00:22:35,290 --> 00:22:37,490
(Intensive Care Unit)

430
00:22:57,650 --> 00:22:58,680
What's this?

431
00:22:59,850 --> 00:23:00,950
Why are tears...

432
00:23:06,260 --> 00:23:09,290
Seo Rin, should I get breakfast ready?

433
00:23:10,490 --> 00:23:11,500
Mrs. Yang.

434
00:23:12,600 --> 00:23:13,600
Do you know what this is?

435
00:23:16,070 --> 00:23:17,300
What? Your palm?

436
00:23:17,300 --> 00:23:20,470
No, these are my tears.

437
00:23:20,740 --> 00:23:22,710
Isn't that weird?

438
00:23:23,240 --> 00:23:25,210
I just suddenly started crying.

439
00:23:25,210 --> 00:23:27,680
And on top of that, my chest hurts.

440
00:23:29,180 --> 00:23:30,480
Am I sick or something?

441
00:23:32,950 --> 00:23:34,450
You don't have a fever.

442
00:23:34,950 --> 00:23:36,890
Should I make you some porridge, then?

443
00:23:37,190 --> 00:23:38,790
No, that's okay.
Just give me a regular meal.

444
00:23:39,320 --> 00:23:41,020
I have to get to work and see my Jun Ho.

445
00:23:49,930 --> 00:23:52,000
Where's Mom?
It's still early in the morning.

446
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:53,400
She already left for work.

447
00:23:53,870 --> 00:23:54,940
Why?

448
00:23:55,370 --> 00:23:57,570
I wanted to ask her something.

449
00:23:57,570 --> 00:23:58,680
What about?

450
00:23:58,840 --> 00:24:00,640
Something weird happened.

451
00:24:00,640 --> 00:24:02,610
I suddenly started crying,

452
00:24:02,780 --> 00:24:04,880
and then out of nowhere,
my chest started to hurt.

453
00:24:05,450 --> 00:24:08,690
I feel like I'm feeling another's emotions
instead of my own.

454
00:24:08,820 --> 00:24:11,490
Sweetie, what's all this about?

455
00:24:11,990 --> 00:24:14,120
That sounds just like twin telepathy.

456
00:24:14,930 --> 00:24:17,790
"Twin telepathy?" What is that?

457
00:24:18,260 --> 00:24:19,300
A twin?

458
00:24:19,460 --> 00:24:23,430
Right. I heard that
twins share emotions, pain,

459
00:24:23,430 --> 00:24:25,670
and anxiety with each other.

460
00:24:26,200 --> 00:24:28,770
It's something I vaguely remember
from a psychology class,

461
00:24:29,270 --> 00:24:31,340
- so I may not be remembering correctly.
- Twins?

462
00:24:31,340 --> 00:24:33,080
Honey, are you sick?

463
00:24:33,080 --> 00:24:35,910
I'm going to have Dr. Kim check you out.

464
00:24:35,980 --> 00:24:38,950
He's right.
It's not like Seo Rin is a twin,

465
00:24:39,320 --> 00:24:41,220
and it would be terrible
if you were actually sick.

466
00:24:41,450 --> 00:24:43,750
But why would you be crying, then?

467
00:24:44,650 --> 00:24:47,020
It's not like there are two of you.

468
00:24:48,060 --> 00:24:49,360
Two of me?

469
00:24:49,990 --> 00:24:51,460
You're not Jang Mi.

470
00:24:52,230 --> 00:24:53,660
You're pretending to be Jang Mi.

471
00:24:53,930 --> 00:24:56,030
- You're not Jang Mi.
- What's with this woman?

472
00:24:57,100 --> 00:24:59,640
Goodness! What am I going to do?

473
00:24:59,670 --> 00:25:01,670
- Gosh.
- Shoot. I dropped it.

474
00:25:02,710 --> 00:25:04,240
Who is this solicitor?

475
00:25:04,410 --> 00:25:05,410
Wait.

476
00:25:05,880 --> 00:25:06,880
Jang Mi.

477
00:25:08,510 --> 00:25:10,150
Oh, you're not Jang Mi.

478
00:25:11,680 --> 00:25:14,820
Seo Rin,
I'm sending Secretary Kim over later.

479
00:25:14,950 --> 00:25:17,420
You need to go get a check-up, okay?

480
00:25:18,090 --> 00:25:19,420
I'm fine, Grandpa.

481
00:25:20,160 --> 00:25:24,090
Grandpa, thank you
for promoting Jun Ho to General Manager.

482
00:25:24,790 --> 00:25:26,460
I'm not crying anymore. I'm so excited!

483
00:25:28,430 --> 00:25:33,070
(Company Bulletin Board)

484
00:25:33,070 --> 00:25:35,370
(Kang Jun Ho is promoted
to General Manager of Brand Kitchen.)

485
00:25:35,370 --> 00:25:36,370
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

486
00:25:36,370 --> 00:25:37,640
Put up the notice with the title,

487
00:25:37,640 --> 00:25:40,210
"Kang Jun Ho, General Manager
of Brand Kitchen at Dream Hotel,"

488
00:25:40,610 --> 00:25:42,150
distribute a press release,

489
00:25:42,850 --> 00:25:45,920
and coordinate with General Manager Kang
to schedule an interview.

490
00:25:47,150 --> 00:25:48,150
Yes, ma'am.

491
00:25:48,220 --> 00:25:50,150
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

492
00:25:56,760 --> 00:25:59,300
Ma'am, you have a visitor.

493
00:26:00,000 --> 00:26:01,000
A visitor?

494
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:05,770
I'm Detective Kim Hyun Soo
from the Yeongseo Police Department.

495
00:26:10,670 --> 00:26:11,680
Team Leader Jin.

496
00:26:12,480 --> 00:26:13,480
What...

497
00:26:13,480 --> 00:26:14,480
Yes.

498
00:26:20,580 --> 00:26:22,290
What in the world is going on?

499
00:26:26,120 --> 00:26:29,630
- What's going on?
- A detective is in the CEO's office.

500
00:26:29,790 --> 00:26:30,890
A detective?

501
00:26:32,160 --> 00:26:34,760
You know Mr. Kang Nam Bong
and Mr. Oh Bok Gil, right?

502
00:26:35,400 --> 00:26:37,300
I'm here regarding a car accident.

503
00:26:37,900 --> 00:26:39,170
I heard about that.

504
00:26:40,070 --> 00:26:41,540
Please, have a seat.

505
00:26:42,940 --> 00:26:44,110
Please bring us some tea.

506
00:26:51,450 --> 00:26:52,480
Please, have some tea.

507
00:26:53,980 --> 00:26:55,190
Thank you.

508
00:27:04,390 --> 00:27:07,600
I have a few questions for you.

509
00:27:10,070 --> 00:27:11,200
And what would those be?

510
00:27:13,440 --> 00:27:15,270
Before Mr. Oh Bok Gil
called Ms. Oh Jang Mi,

511
00:27:15,610 --> 00:27:19,740
the last person he spoke with was you.

512
00:27:21,310 --> 00:27:22,650
What was the nature of your conversation?

513
00:27:47,100 --> 00:27:48,610
(The First Man)

514
00:27:48,670 --> 00:27:51,010
There must have been
some kind of accident.

515
00:27:51,340 --> 00:27:52,640
I've got to check it out.

516
00:27:53,040 --> 00:27:55,850
Did you say Route 21 in Yeongseo-myeon,
toward Taean?

517
00:27:56,480 --> 00:28:00,050
When you last spoke with your father,
did he mention anything?

518
00:28:00,580 --> 00:28:02,290
He said he saw someone
who looked just like me.

519
00:28:02,450 --> 00:28:05,320
I have a question about a news report...

520
00:28:05,320 --> 00:28:06,720
on an incident that happened
a few days ago.

521
00:28:06,790 --> 00:28:08,890
What's Mom's connection to this man?

522
00:28:09,460 --> 00:28:10,930
Is she really the mom I know?

